HEADWORD: Slub
<hw>Slub</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Etymol.
uncertain.]</ety> <def>A roll of wool slightly twisted; a rove; --
called also <altname>slubbing</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slub</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Slub
<hw>Slub</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Slubbed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Slubbing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To draw out and twist slightly;
-- said of slivers of wool.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slubber</ent>⟦br⟧
